    {
      "id": "/page/0/Text/2",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">Options on broad market ETFs, such as the Nasdaq 100 Index Trust (QQQQ) and the S&amp;P 500 Index Trust (SPY), are the most widely traded contracts in the US markets. As of this writing, their daily volumes far exceed those of options on most individual stocks. Owing to this wide acceptance, QQQQ and ETF options have recently been given quarterly expirations in addition to the standard expirations for equity options. Options on sector ETFs, such as the S&amp;P Financials Index (XLF) or the Merrill Lynch HOLDR (SMH), are also highly liquid.</p>",
      "page": 187,
      "polygon": [
        [
          74.1873417721519,
          192.5498046875
        ],
        [
          286.4609375,
          192.5498046875
        ],
        [
          286.4609375,
          328.40234375
        ],
        [
          74.1873417721519,
          328.40234375
