    {
      "id": "/page/0/Text/3",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">If we denote by <math display=\"inline\">B</math> the value of the basket of stocks at the expiration date of the option, a basket call has payoff given by <math display=\"inline\">\\max(B - K, 0)</math> and a basket put has payoff <math display=\"inline\">\\max(K - B, 0)</math>, where K is the strike price. Most exchange-traded ETF options are physically settled. Index options tend to be cash settled. Over-the-counter basket options, especially those embedded in structured notes, are cash settled.</p>",
      "page": 187,
      "polygon": [
        [
          74.1873417721519,
          330.53081510934396
        ],
        [
          286.4609375,
          330.53081510934396
        ],
        [
          286.4609375,
          431.8564453125
        ],
        [
          74.1873417721519,
          431.8564453125
