    {
      "id": "/page/0/TextInlineMath/12",
      "block_type": "TextInlineMath",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"TextInlineMath\">The notion of <i>implied correlation</i> is sometimes used to quote basket option prices. The market convention is to assume (for quoting purposes) that <math display=\"inline\">\\rho_{ij} \\equiv \\rho</math>, a constant. It then follows from equation (1) that the implied correlation of a basket option is</p>",
      "page": 187,
      "polygon": [
        [
          301.24556962025315,
          275.0675944333996
        ],
        [
          513.3164556962025,
          275.0675944333996
        ],
        [
          513.3164556962025,
          330.9794921875
        ],
        [
          301.24556962025315,
          330.9794921875
        ]
      ],
      "bbox": [
        301.24556962025315,
        275.0675944333996,
        513.3164556962025,
        330.9794921875
      ],
      "section_hierarchy": {
        "2": "/page/0/SectionHeader/0"
      },
      "images": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "/page/0/Equation/13",
      "block_type": "Equation",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Equation\"><math display=\"block\">\\rho \\equiv \\frac{\\sigma_B^2 - \\sum_{i=1}^n p_i^2 \\sigma_i^2}{\\sum_{i \\neq j} p_i p_j \\sigma_i \\sigma_j} = \\frac{\\sigma_B^2 - \\sum_{i=1}^n p_i^2 \\sigma_i^2}{\\left(\\sum_{i=1}^n p_i \\sigma_i\\right)^2 - \\sum_{i=1}^n p_i^2 \\sigma_i^2}</math><math display=\"block\">\\approx \\frac{\\sigma_B^2}{\\left(\\sum_{i=1}^n p_i \\sigma_i\\right)^2} \\tag{4}</math></p>",
      "page": 187,
      "polygon": [
        [
          310.453125,
          344.6015625
        ],
        [
          512.796875,
          344.6015625
        ],
        [
          512.796875,
          463.88671875
        ],
        [
          310.453125,
          463.88671875
        ]
      ],
      "bbox": [
        310.453125,
        344.6015625,
        512.796875,
        463.88671875
      ],
      "section_hierarchy": {
        "2": "/page/0/SectionHeader/0"
      },
      "images": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "/page/0/Text/14",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">Implied correlation is the market convention for quoting the implied volatility of a basket option as a fraction of the weighted average of implied volatilities of the components.</p>",
      "page": 187,
      "polygon": [
        [
          301.24556962025315,
          472.93638170974157
        ],
        [
          513.3164556962025,
          472.93638170974157
        ],
        [
          513.3164556962025,
          516.90234375
        ],
        [
          301.24556962025315,
          516.90234375
        ]
      ],
      "bbox": [
        301.24556962025315,
        472.93638170974157,
        513.3164556962025,
        516.90234375
      ],
      "section_hierarchy": {
